Question: Design a logo and social media ads for our client, Mock & Proper.

Mock & Proper is a new brand making its own line of low or no alcohol wines and fine spirits. The goal is to reach a broader audience with something that feels elevated but doesn’t come with the usual baggage of drinking, or the stuffiness of other alcohol brands.

They’re targeting people in their late 20s to early 40s. Health-conscious, socially active, digitally engaged, into good design and better life choices. Young professionals, creatives, and wellness types who still want the ritual of a drink without the aftereffects.

The problem they’re solving is clear. Most alcohol alternatives feel like a compromise. Mock & Proper wants to offer something that still feels social and sensory but fits with a healthier lifestyle.

The campaign slogan is “Impeccably Improper.” The idea is a mix of upscale speakeasy and playful irreverence. A bit of a tension between the "mock" (making fun of/having fun/joking around) and "proper" (distilleries, brewers, winemakers tend to be uptight). It’s a brand that takes quality seriously but doesn’t take itself too seriously. Refined and cheeky, at the same time.

